summary: Most on brand thing I’ve done
body:
Most on brand thing I’ve done

So as you likely don’t know, I am a senior in high school. I am a “good kid”. Which means I don’t do drugs, drink, or skip school. Wanna know what I did today?


I skipped school to go buy Kingdom of Ash. I purposely overslept so that Barnes and Noble would be open and went there before I went to school.


When I got to school at 11:30 my friend laughed and said it was the most on brand reason for me to skip school ever.


So go me, first time ever skipping school and it’s to buy a book.

summary: So in honor of Kingdom of Ash coming out I was rereading The Assasins Blade and I found a lil bit. These words seem like they...
body:
So in honor of Kingdom of Ash coming out I was rereading The Assasins Blade and I found a lil bit. These words seem like they are about to come right back around and I don’t think my heart can handle that.


Also, I am just very split on my excitement/fear for KoA. Like on one hand, hopefully we’ll get some fucking resolution. On the other hand, it means the series is over and my heart will likely be shattered on the floor. But ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ what can ya do (lots of things, but mainly cry)


I’ll see you all soon, I’ll probably be crying over KoA by then so see ya.

summary: KoA
body:
KoA

Happy Kingdom of Ash release date everyone. It sure feels like the end of an era, but I cannot wait for the next one. I just want to say thank you to all the amazing artists out there providing untalented fans (like myself) with mind-blowing art. And of course to Sarah J. Maas for the worlds and characters she has brought and continues to bring to us. Thank you, your books make me and my life better.
